wfDvmrpBaseCreate.name: wfDvmrpBaseCreate
wfDvmrpBaseCreate.description: This entry will provide the base configuration for the DVMRP multicast support on the router.

wfDvmrpBaseEnable.name: wfDvmrpBaseEnable
wfDvmrpBaseEnable.description: Enable or disable DVMRP support in router

wfDvmrpBaseFullUpdateInterval.name: wfDvmrpBaseFullUpdateInterval
wfDvmrpBaseFullUpdateInterval.description: Full update interval. This value specifies, in seconds, how often routing messages containing complete routing tables are sent.

wfDvmrpBaseTriggeredUpdateInterval.name: wfDvmrpBaseTriggeredUpdateInterval
wfDvmrpBaseTriggeredUpdateInterval.description: Triggered update interval. This value specifies, in seconds, how often triggered routing messages are sent; this represents the minimum amount of time between these type of messages. Triggered updates are sent between full update; the timers restart when a full update is sent so this value should be less than the full update rate.

wfDvmrpBaseLeafTimeout.name: wfDvmrpBaseLeafTimeout
wfDvmrpBaseLeafTimeout.description: Leaf timeout. This value specifies, in seconds, the virtual interface hold down timer.

wfDvmrpBaseNeighborTimeout.name: wfDvmrpBaseNeighborTimeout
wfDvmrpBaseNeighborTimeout.description: Neighbor timeout. This value specifies, in seconds, how long a router neighbor is considered 'up' without confirmation.

wfDvmrpBaseRouteExpirationTimeout.name: wfDvmrpBaseRouteExpirationTimeout
wfDvmrpBaseRouteExpirationTimeout.description: Route Expiration timeout. This value specifies, in seconds, how long a route is considered valid without confirmation; this represents the duration of time that this route will be used.

wfDvmrpBaseGarbageTimeout.name: wfDvmrpBaseGarbageTimeout
wfDvmrpBaseGarbageTimeout.description: Garbage timeout. This value specifies, in seconds, how long a route exists without confirmation; this represents the duration of time that this route will be included in routing updates. This value must be greater than the route expiration timeout.

wfDvmrpBaseEstimatedRoutes.name: wfDvmrpBaseEstimatedRoutes
wfDvmrpBaseEstimatedRoutes.description: Estimated number of routes, per slot. This is used for pre-allocating routing tables. Note that routes are kept on a per-source network basis, independent of multicast group. This number must include a route for every local network that has a CCT configured for multicasting.

wfDvmrpBaseNeighborProbeInterval.name: wfDvmrpBaseNeighborProbeInterval
wfDvmrpBaseNeighborProbeInterval.description: Neighbor probe interval: how often to send a probe on VIFs

wfDvmrpBaseRouteSwitchTimeout.name: wfDvmrpBaseRouteSwitchTimeout
wfDvmrpBaseRouteSwitchTimeout.description: Route switch timeout. How long to wait, without receiving a subsequent route update from the original neighbor, before switching to a different neighbor.

wfDvmrpBaseActualRoutes.name: wfDvmrpBaseActualRoutes
wfDvmrpBaseActualRoutes.description: Count of number of entries currently in route table

wfDvmrpBaseDebugLevel.name: wfDvmrpBaseDebugLevel
wfDvmrpBaseDebugLevel.description: Turn DVMRP log ON or OFF for DVMRP debuging messages The levels are: NO_DISPLAY_LOG 0x0001 - Reserved ROUTE_UPDATE_LOG 0x0002 - Displays all routing table events CACHE_ADD_LOG 0x0004 - Displays events relating to addition of cache entry by the cache gate CACHE_DELETE_LOG 0x0008 - Displays all events relating to deletion of cache entry CACHE_CHANGE_LOG 0x0010 - Displays all events relating to updates of cache entries CACHE_DATA_LOG 0x0020 - obsolete PRUNE_MSG_LOG 0x0040 - Display router received pruning related messages, including prunes, grafts, graft_acks, and neighbor reset PRUNE_XMIT_LOG 0x0080 - Display a messaged when a initial prune state is established for a (src, group). IGMP_COM_LOG 0x0100 - Display communication events between IGMP and DVMRP, events including some hosts joining a group, and all hosts leaving a group. DVMRP_XMIT_LOG 0x0200 - Display transmission events by the router, e.g, prune, grafts... CACHE_NO_GH_LOG 0x0400 - Display buffer forwarding to non-existing main or remote cache gate. CACHE_DBG_LOG 0x0800 - Display general debugging messaages MEM_DBG_LOG 0x1000 - Display dvmrp memory usage activities INTEROP_DBG_LOG 0x2000 - Display dvmrp mospf debug CACHE_BASE_ADD_LOG 0x4000 - Obsolete CACHE_VIF_ADD_LOG 0x8000 - Obsolete CACHE_BASE_DELETE_LOG 0x10000 - Obsolete CACHE_VIF_DELETE_LOG 0x20000 - Obsolete MTRACE_UPDATE_LOG 0x40000 - Displays mtrace update info NEIGHBOR_UPDATE_LOG 0x80000 - Display events relating to addition, deletion and update of neighbor's info MTM_INTERFACE_LOG 0x100000 - Display events relating to MTM-DVMRP interface, events as MTM inbound, outbound interact with DVMRP and entries deletion/addition. ROUTE_ADD_LOG 0x200000 - ROUTE_DEL_LOG 0x400000 - REMOTE_CACHE_ADD_LOG 0x800000 - Display addition event for the outgoing interface of (source, group) cache entry REMOTE_CACHE_DELETE_LOG 0x1000000 - Display deletion event for the outgoing interface of (source, group) cache entry RX_CONFLICT_ROUTE_INFO_LOG 0x2000000 - Display received conflict route information

wfDvmrpBasePruningEnable.name: wfDvmrpBasePruningEnable
wfDvmrpBasePruningEnable.description: Enable or Disable Pruning functionality at the Base level

wfDvmrpBaseFragmentMtuThreshold.name: wfDvmrpBaseFragmentMtuThreshold
wfDvmrpBaseFragmentMtuThreshold.description: the default value is the CSMACD_MTU, and the MINiMUN is X25_DDN_MTU. Both are taken from dp.h

wfDvmrpBaseMaxRoutes.name: wfDvmrpBaseMaxRoutes
wfDvmrpBaseMaxRoutes.description: Max number of routes, per slot. This is used to limit the size of routing tables. Note that routes are kept on a per-source network basis, independent of multicast group. This number must include a route for every local network that has a CCT configured for multicasting.

wfDvmrpBasePolicyEnable.name: wfDvmrpBasePolicyEnable
wfDvmrpBasePolicyEnable.description: Enable or Disable route policy functionality at the Base level

wfDvmrpBaseHolddownEnable.name: wfDvmrpBaseHolddownEnable
wfDvmrpBaseHolddownEnable.description: Enable or Disable holddown of deleted routes.

wfDvmrpCircuitEntry.name: wfDvmrpCircuitEntry
wfDvmrpCircuitEntry.description: One instance of this object exists for every CCT that supports this feature. The instance ID for this object will be the circuit number.

wfDvmrpCircuitEnable.name: wfDvmrpCircuitEnable
wfDvmrpCircuitEnable.description: Enable or disable DVMRP on this circuit

wfDvmrpCircuitState.name: wfDvmrpCircuitState
wfDvmrpCircuitState.description: The current state of the DVMRP interface. Invalid indicates an error in processing the configuration record.

wfDvmrpCircuitRouteEnable.name: wfDvmrpCircuitRouteEnable
wfDvmrpCircuitRouteEnable.description: Enable/disble this circuit for routing. If enabled, this circuit will be used to propogate routing information, information about this circuit will be incorporated into routing updates, and multicast datagrams will be forwarded 'in native mode' (e.g. as multicast datagrams) via this circuit. If disabled, this circuit exists only to support unicast tunnels; in this case, all other paramters are ignored.

wfDvmrpCircuitMetric.name: wfDvmrpCircuitMetric
wfDvmrpCircuitMetric.description: Metric. This value represents the cost of this interface; the cost of using this hop. This value must be smaller than the route infinity value

wfDvmrpCircuitRouteThreshold.name: wfDvmrpCircuitRouteThreshold
wfDvmrpCircuitRouteThreshold.description: Threshold. This value can be used to filter out datagrams that are being forwarded to a neighboring router; if the IP TTL is not >= the threshold, the datagram is dropped by this router

wfDvmrpCircuitInPkts.name: wfDvmrpCircuitInPkts
wfDvmrpCircuitInPkts.description: Number of datagrams received on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitOutPkts.name: wfDvmrpCircuitOutPkts
wfDvmrpCircuitOutPkts.description: Number of datagrams send on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitInRouteUpdates.name: wfDvmrpCircuitInRouteUpdates
wfDvmrpCircuitInRouteUpdates.description: Number of DVMRP route update messages received

wfDvmrpCircuitOutRouteUpdates.name: wfDvmrpCircuitOutRouteUpdates
wfDvmrpCircuitOutRouteUpdates.description: Number of DVMRP route update messages sent

wfDvmrpCircuitInPktDiscards.name: wfDvmrpCircuitInPktDiscards
wfDvmrpCircuitInPktDiscards.description: Number of inbound datagrams discarded due to route not found

wfDvmrpCircuitOutPktDiscards.name: wfDvmrpCircuitOutPktDiscards
wfDvmrpCircuitOutPktDiscards.description: Number of outbound datagrams discarded due to route not found

wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheSize.name: wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheSize
wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheSize.description: Maximum number of entries allowed in the Forwarding table at one time. there is a Forwarding table per vif

wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheTTL.name: wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheTTL
wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheTTL.description: The time_to_live for the Forwarding table entries in seconds .

wfDvmrpCircuitAdvertiseSelf.name: wfDvmrpCircuitAdvertiseSelf
wfDvmrpCircuitAdvertiseSelf.description: If enabled the router will advertise itself as one of the source net. If not enabled the router will not advertise itself as one of the source net.

wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheEntries.name: wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheEntries
wfDvmrpCircuitFwdCacheEntries.description: The most up to date number of entries in the forwarding cache

wfDvmrpCircuitInPrunePkts.name: wfDvmrpCircuitInPrunePkts
wfDvmrpCircuitInPrunePkts.description: Number of PRUNE datagrams received on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitOutPrunePkts.name: wfDvmrpCircuitOutPrunePkts
wfDvmrpCircuitOutPrunePkts.description: Number of PRUNE datagrams send on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitInGraftPkts.name: wfDvmrpCircuitInGraftPkts
wfDvmrpCircuitInGraftPkts.description: Number of GRAFT datagrams received on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitOutGraftPkts.name: wfDvmrpCircuitOutGraftPkts
wfDvmrpCircuitOutGraftPkts.description: Number of GRAFT datagrams send on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitInGraftAckPkts.name: wfDvmrpCircuitInGraftAckPkts
wfDvmrpCircuitInGraftAckPkts.description: Number of GRAFT_ACK datagrams received on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitOutGraftAckPkts.name: wfDvmrpCircuitOutGraftAckPkts
wfDvmrpCircuitOutGraftAckPkts.description: Number of GRAFT_ACK datagrams send on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitDefaultRouteSupply.name: wfDvmrpCircuitDefaultRouteSupply
wfDvmrpCircuitDefaultRouteSupply.description: enabled : Send the default route, 0.0.0.0 if learned, form this interface. disabled: no default route is sent from this interface. generate: generate default route, 0.0.0.0 from this interface.

wfDvmrpCircuitDefaultRouteListen.name: wfDvmrpCircuitDefaultRouteListen
wfDvmrpCircuitDefaultRouteListen.description: Receive the default route, 0.0.0.0 on this interface

wfDvmrpCircuitReportDependProbe.name: wfDvmrpCircuitReportDependProbe
wfDvmrpCircuitReportDependProbe.description: This is to control accepting the route report. According to the protocol, dvmrp should send probe packet before sending the route report packet to the neighbors. But some vendor implementation did not send probes before sending reports. Enable: only process the routes from the neighbor sending probes. Disable: No Dependency (no restriction).

wfDvmrpCircuitPruneLifeTime.name: wfDvmrpCircuitPruneLifeTime
wfDvmrpCircuitPruneLifeTime.description: The life time of the prune message the router sends to its neighbor in seconds.

wfDvmrpCircuitAcceptAggregateRoutes.name: wfDvmrpCircuitAcceptAggregateRoutes
wfDvmrpCircuitAcceptAggregateRoutes.description: Count of number of routes received have been aggregated to the specific aggregate route currently in route table for this interface.

wfDvmrpCircuitAnnounceAggregatedRoutes.name: wfDvmrpCircuitAnnounceAggregatedRoutes
wfDvmrpCircuitAnnounceAggregatedRoutes.description: Count of number of routes have been aggregated to the specific aggregate route for advertisement currently in route table for this interface.

wfDvmrpTunnelEntry.name: wfDvmrpTunnelEntry
wfDvmrpTunnelEntry.description: This object is used to specify the set of 'multicast tunnels', unicast pipes that are used to send IP multicast datagrams to remote network multicast routers via intermediate routers that may not support this style of IP multicasting. One instance of this object exists for every separate tunnel destination. The instance identifier is the IP address of the remote router neighbor and the local circuit number.

wfDvmrpTunnelState.name: wfDvmrpTunnelState
wfDvmrpTunnelState.description: The current state of the DVMRP tunnel interface. Invalid indicates an error in processing the configuration record.

wfDvmrpTunnelCCT.name: wfDvmrpTunnelCCT
wfDvmrpTunnelCCT.description: The multicast circuit associated with this tunnel.

wfDvmrpTunnelRemoteRouterIpAddress.name: wfDvmrpTunnelRemoteRouterIpAddress
wfDvmrpTunnelRemoteRouterIpAddress.description: (unicast) IP address of remote network router neighbor.

wfDvmrpTunnelEncapsMode.name: wfDvmrpTunnelEncapsMode
wfDvmrpTunnelEncapsMode.description: Will these tunnelled datagrams be encapsulated within an IP datagram, or will they be loosely encapsulated using the LSSR option (for the latter, refer to RFC 1075; this is needed for backward compatibility)

wfDvmrpTunnelThreshold.name: wfDvmrpTunnelThreshold
wfDvmrpTunnelThreshold.description: Threshold for forwarding through this tunnel; if TTL < threshold, the datagram is dropped.

wfDvmrpTunnelInPkts.name: wfDvmrpTunnelInPkts
wfDvmrpTunnelInPkts.description: Number of datagrams received on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelOutPkts.name: wfDvmrpTunnelOutPkts
wfDvmrpTunnelOutPkts.description: Number of datagrams send on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelInRouteUpdates.name: wfDvmrpTunnelInRouteUpdates
wfDvmrpTunnelInRouteUpdates.description: Number of DVMRP route update messages received

wfDvmrpTunnelOutRouteUpdates.name: wfDvmrpTunnelOutRouteUpdates
wfDvmrpTunnelOutRouteUpdates.description: Number of DVMRP route update messages sent

wfDvmrpTunnelInPktDiscards.name: wfDvmrpTunnelInPktDiscards
wfDvmrpTunnelInPktDiscards.description: Number of inbound datagrams discarded due to route not found or due to invalid inner address (dest address != multicast)

wfDvmrpTunnelOutPktDiscards.name: wfDvmrpTunnelOutPktDiscards
wfDvmrpTunnelOutPktDiscards.description: Number of outbound datagrams discarded due to route not found

wfDvmrpTunnelLocalRouterIpAddress.name: wfDvmrpTunnelLocalRouterIpAddress
wfDvmrpTunnelLocalRouterIpAddress.description: (unicast) IP address of local network router. To support multinet.

wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheSize.name: wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheSize
wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheSize.description: Maximum number of entries allowed in the Forwarding table at one time. there is a Forwarding table per vif

wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheTTL.name: wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheTTL
wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheTTL.description: The time_to_live for the Forwarding table entries in seconds .

wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheEntries.name: wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheEntries
wfDvmrpTunnelFwdCacheEntries.description: The most up to date number of entries in the forwarding cache

wfDvmrpTunnelInPrunePkts.name: wfDvmrpTunnelInPrunePkts
wfDvmrpTunnelInPrunePkts.description: Number of PRUNE datagrams received on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelOutPrunePkts.name: wfDvmrpTunnelOutPrunePkts
wfDvmrpTunnelOutPrunePkts.description: Number of PRUNE datagrams send on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelInGraftPkts.name: wfDvmrpTunnelInGraftPkts
wfDvmrpTunnelInGraftPkts.description: Number of GRAFT datagrams received on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelOutGraftPkts.name: wfDvmrpTunnelOutGraftPkts
wfDvmrpTunnelOutGraftPkts.description: Number of GRAFT datagrams send on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelInGraftAckPkts.name: wfDvmrpTunnelInGraftAckPkts
wfDvmrpTunnelInGraftAckPkts.description: Number of GRAFT_ACK datagrams received on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelOutGraftAckPkts.name: wfDvmrpTunnelOutGraftAckPkts
wfDvmrpTunnelOutGraftAckPkts.description: Number of GRAFT_ACK datagrams send on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelDefaultRouteSupply.name: wfDvmrpTunnelDefaultRouteSupply
wfDvmrpTunnelDefaultRouteSupply.description: Send the default route, 0.0.0.0 on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelDefaultRouteListen.name: wfDvmrpTunnelDefaultRouteListen
wfDvmrpTunnelDefaultRouteListen.description: Receive the default route, 0.0.0.0 on this interface

wfDvmrpTunnelCtrlMsgMode.name: wfDvmrpTunnelCtrlMsgMode
wfDvmrpTunnelCtrlMsgMode.description: Dvmrp tunneling control messages encapsulated type. noencaps is the mode that control messages are sent in regular igmp packets with ip protocol type set to IP_PROTOCOL_IGMP. encaps is the mode that control messages are encapsed inside ip packets with ip protocol type set to IP_PROTOCOL_IPINIP. All DVMRP messages sent across tunnels will be encapsulated in the same way as data packets in this mode.

wfDvmrpTunnelReportDependProbe.name: wfDvmrpTunnelReportDependProbe
wfDvmrpTunnelReportDependProbe.description: This is to control accepting the route report. According to the protocol, dvmrp should send probe packet before sending the route report packet to the neighbors. But some vendor implementations do not send probes before sending reports. Enable: only process the routes from the neighbor sending probes. Disable: No Dependency (no restriction).

wfDvmrpTunnelPruneLifeTime.name: wfDvmrpTunnelPruneLifeTime
wfDvmrpTunnelPruneLifeTime.description: The life time of the prune message the router send to its neighbor in seconds.

wfDvmrpTunnelAcceptAggregateRoutes.name: wfDvmrpTunnelAcceptAggregateRoutes
wfDvmrpTunnelAcceptAggregateRoutes.description: Count of number of routes received have been aggregated to the specific aggregate route currently in route table for this interface.

wfDvmrpTunnelAnnounceAggregatedRoutes.name: wfDvmrpTunnelAnnounceAggregatedRoutes
wfDvmrpTunnelAnnounceAggregatedRoutes.description: Count of number of routes have been aggregated to the specific aggregate route for advertisement currently in route table for this interface.

wfDvmrpRouteEntryTable.name: wfDvmrpRouteEntryTable
wfDvmrpRouteEntryTable.description: MIB proxy: main DVMRP routing table

wfDvmrpRouteEntry.name: wfDvmrpRouteEntry
wfDvmrpRouteEntry.description: Supported by mib proxy. One entry exists for each active route.

wfDvmrpRouteSourceMask.name: wfDvmrpRouteSourceMask
wfDvmrpRouteSourceMask.description: Mask for the specified source network

wfDvmrpRouteNextHopRouter.name: wfDvmrpRouteNextHopRouter
wfDvmrpRouteNextHopRouter.description: Next hop multicast router to the specified source network; we consider this neighboring router to be on the shortest path to the source. Note that this neighboring router may be a tunnel endpoint.

wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceCCT.name: wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceCCT
wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceCCT.description: Next hop interface (CCT) to the specified source router; we consider this interface to be on the shortest path to the source.

wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceTunnelId.name: wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceTunnelId
wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceTunnelId.description: Next hop interface (tunnel id) to the specified source router; we consider this interface to be on the shortest path to the source.

wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceLocalTunnelI.name: wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceLocalTunnelId
wfDvmrpRouteNextHopInterfaceLocalTunnelI.description: Next hop interface (local tunnel id) to the specified source router; we consider this interface to be on the shortest path to the source.

wfDvmrpRouteState.name: wfDvmrpRouteState
wfDvmrpRouteState.description: Set of flags indicating state of entry. Note that the router uses this field as a bit mask. 0x8000 Network is local to this router 0x4000 Route is being timed 0x2000 Route is garbaged

wfDvmrpRouteProtocol.name: wfDvmrpRouteProtocol
wfDvmrpRouteProtocol.description: current route protocol dvmrp (2) or mospf (4) or internal (6) which is the route from unicast and incoming interface no i dvmrp configure, if dvmrp is configured then the protocol will be set to 2, see wfIgmpRoutingProtocol

wfDvmrpRouteType.name: wfDvmrpRouteType
wfDvmrpRouteType.description: The orginal route source from. If it is from pure dvmrp route (0x0001) unicast best route (0x0002) unciast route but has dvmrp interface (0x0003) ospf(0x0004) ospf best route (0x0006) ospf ase route (0x0008)

wfDvmrpRouteAggregatedType.name: wfDvmrpRouteAggregatedType
wfDvmrpRouteAggregatedType.description: Route Aggregated types : 0 - normal route 1 - inbound aggregated route 2 - outbound aggregated route 4 - inbound aggregate route 8 - outbound aggregate route

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceEntryTable.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceEntryTable
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceEntryTable.description: MIB proxy: DVMRP VIF routing table

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceEntry.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceEntry
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceEntry.description: Supported by mib proxy. One entry exists for each virtual interface on an active route. It is associated with a route via the source network/ net mask fields. The instance ID includes tunnel ID, which is 0 for non-tunnel interfaces.

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSourceMask.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSourceMask
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSourceMask.description: Mask for the specified source network

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceCCT.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceCCT
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceCCT.description: circuit number with which this route is associated

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceLoc.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceLocalTunnelId
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceLoc.description: Tunnel ID for tunnelled interfaces. This value is zero for non-tunnelled interfaces, otherwise it contains the local IP address of the tunnel.

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceTun.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceTunnelId
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceNextHopInterfaceTun.description: Tunnel ID for tunnelled interfaces. This value is zero for non-tunnelled interfaces, otherwise it contains the remote IP address of the tunnel.

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceState.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceState
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceState.description: state of interface for this route. Note that the router uses this field as a bit mask. 0x8000 - interface is leaf 0x4000 - interface is child 0x2000 - interface is in hold-down state 0x1000 - interface has loop neighbor for this route

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceDominantRouter.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceDominantRouter
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceDominantRouter.description: dominant router address for virtual interface

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSubordinateRouter.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSubordinateRouter
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSubordinateRouter.description: subordinate router address for virtual interface

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceHoldDownTimer.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceHoldDownTimer
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceHoldDownTimer.description: Current value of hold down timer, used to determine if interface is for leaf or non-leaf network. Non-leaf network means that a local network router considers us to be in the shortest path to the source (they have sent us a route update with metric >= infinity).

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSPInDiscards.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSPInDiscards
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSPInDiscards.description: Count of inbound packets discarded because interface not on shortest path

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSPOutDiscards.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSPOutDiscards
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceSPOutDiscards.description: Count of outbound packets discarded because interface not on shortest path

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceThresholdOutDiscard.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceThresholdOutDiscards
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceThresholdOutDiscard.description: Count of outbound packets discarded because of threshold

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceInSuccessfulPkts.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceInSuccessfulPkts
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceInSuccessfulPkts.description: Count of inbound packets accepted for forwarding

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceOutSuccessfulPkts.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceOutSuccessfulPkts
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceOutSuccessfulPkts.description: Count of outbound packets accepted for forwarding

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentCCT.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentCCT
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentCCT.description: circuit number with which this route is associated;parent VIF

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentLocalTunnelId.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentLocalTunnelId
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentLocalTunnelId.description: Tunnel ID for tunnelled interfaces. This value is zero for non-tunnelled interfaces, otherwise it contains the local IP address of the tunnel; parent VIF.

wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentTunnelId.name: wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentTunnelId
wfDvmrpRouteInterfaceParentTunnelId.description: Tunnel ID for tunnelled interfaces. This value is zero for non-tunnelled interfaces, otherwise it contains the remote IP address of the tunnel; parent VIF.

wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterEntry.name: wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterEntry
wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterEntry.description: This entry is used to indentify the known neighboring routers for a circuit. This object will be indentified by circuit number, tunnel id (to identify local interface), and the IP address of the neighbor.

wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterLocalTunnelId.name: wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterLocalTunnelId
wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterLocalTunnelId.description: Tunnel Id for interface. This value is zero for non- tunnelled interfaces, otherwise it contains the IP address of the local tunnel endpoint.

wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterTunnelId.name: wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterTunnelId
wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterTunnelId.description: Tunnel Id for interface. This value is zero for non- tunnelled interfaces, otherwise it contains the IP address of the remote tunnel endpoint.

wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterState.name: wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterState
wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterState.description: State of neighbor. The router uses this as a bit mask. 0x8000 - Neighbor is being timed

wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterMajorVersion.name: wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterMajorVersion
wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterMajorVersion.description: The neighboring router's major DVMRP version number.

wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterMinorVersion.name: wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterMinorVersion
wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterMinorVersion.description: The neighboring router's minor DVMRP version number.

wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterCapabilities.name: wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterCapabilities
wfDvmrpNeighboringRouterCapabilities.description: This object describes the neighboring router's capabilities. The leaf bit indicates that the neighbor has only one interface with neighbors. The prune bit indicates that the neighbor supports pruning. The generationID bit indicates that the neighbor sends its generationID in Probe messages. The mtrace bit indicates that the neighbor can handle mtrace requests.
